COVID-19 INDIA

This is a detailed data analysis of Covid-19 Data in india , Aiming to extract insights on variables effecting State-Wise performace in combating the pandemic and reaching factual conclusions supported by data .

The Data Used was obtained from the following links :
Covid-19 India Dataset - https://www.kaggle.com/sudalairajkumar/covid19-in-india?select=covid_19_india.csv
India shp file - https://codeload.github.com/arka1985/MAP_INDIA_R/zip/master
Indian Rural Population - https://hetv.org/india/india-rural-urban-distribution-of-population-2011.xls
Indian Population Dataset https://storage.googleapis.com/kaggle-data-sets/557629%2F1489204%2Fbundle%2Far

State-Wise Confirmed Cases per Million

State-Wise COVID-19 Tests Performed Per Million

The plots reveal that most states in India seem to be performing well against COVID-19 but tests performed by these states reveal that due to lack of testing , there is a lack data to map the spread of disease in such states Whereas states such as Delhi , Arunanchal Pradesh and Goa seem to be worst hit by the pandemic only to reveal that these states have performed the most tests per million and thus have a greater grip on the spread of the pandemic inside the states

Population Density of Each State


POPULATION DENSITY

Population Density does not seem to have a major pattern in the performance of states against the pandemic as seen states having comparatively lower density are mostly at the bottom left corner of the plot with some towards the top right , Similarly Denser states are also spread allover the graph

Rural Density Of Each State


RURAL DENSITY

The plot reveals a clear pattern showing the significant effect of rural population on each state’s performance against the pandemic , with states with higher rural proportion residing mostly towards the bottom left whereas urban states are towards the top right
 Though the plot also suggests that there are outliers such as Arunanchal Pradesh , Andaman & Nicobar Islands and Andhra Pradesh which are performing relatively better despite higher rural population
Similarly States such as Chandigarh , Kerala and Maharashtra are relatively in worse position despite being mostly urban



CONCLUSION

Most states in India have improved their overall testing per million

Yet some states have performed significantly better than others while some have done worse ,

This goes to show that although their are multiple varibales which effect the performance of a region against a pandemic their is a significant scope for good management and bad management by respective state governance and authorities.
